Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C and boil your kettle. Pour the @water{400%ml} into a #measuring jug{} and add the @chicken stock powder{1/2}. Stir to dissolve. Heat a splash of @olive oil{1.5%tbsp} in an #ovenproof pan{} over medium-high heat. Add the @chicken thigh{140%g}(diced) and fry, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> TIP: Do this in batches if necessary, you want the chicken to brown not stew.

Return all the chicken to the pan and add the @chorizo{30%g}, stir-fry for ~{2%minutes}. Stir in the @Arborio rice{175%g} to coat it in the oil, then pour in the @white wine vinegar{6%tsp} and allow to evaporate. Add the stock and bring to the boil, then remove from the heat. Cover with a tight fitting lid (or some foil) and pop the dish on the top shelf of your #oven{} for ~{20%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim the @baby gem lettuce{1/2}. Halve the lettuce lengthways, then thinly slice widthways. Halve the @cherry plum tomatoes{200%g}. Trim the @cucumber{1/2}, quarter it lengthways, then chop widthways into small pieces. Combine the lettuce, tomatoes and cucumber in a #bowl{}. Mix the @garlic mayonnaise{1} in a bowl with a splash of water to loosen it up slightly. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Put the @pine nuts{15%g} in a #freezer bag{} and roughly crush using the bottom of a #saucepan{}. Tip into a #small bowl{}. Roughly chop the @basil{12%leaves}(roughly chopped, stalks and all) and add this to the bowl. Stir in half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and @olive oil{1.5%tbsp} until you have a drizzling consistency.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and gently fold through the @unsalted butter{30%g} and @grated hard Italian style cheese{(remaining 40g)}. Stir through the @baby spinach{62.5%g} until wilted.

> TIP: If the kids don't like spinach, serve theirs before adding the spinach.

Divide the chopped salad between two #bowls{} and dress half with the garlic mayonnaise dressing (unless the kids are really adventurous, in which case dress it all!).

Serve the baked risotto in bowls with the salad on the side (dressed or not). Finish with a little of the drizzle. Enjoy!